<Action id="52193" issue="34647" author="jvsclp" type="comment" created="2018-10-12 21:13:53.0" updateauthor="jvsclp" updated="2018-10-12 21:14:12.0"> <body><! CDATA The problem occurs with the volume mount on line 507 of the makefile. MINGW64 mangles the name before handing it off to Docker. *{{-v $(abspath .):/opt/gopath/src/$(PACKAGE_NAME) -u $(shell id -u):$(shell id -g)}}*   Adding a forward slash before the abspath call corrects the name mangling and resolves the issue using MINGW64 on Windows 10. *{{-v {color:#ff0000}/{color}$(abspath .):/opt/gopath/src/$(PACKAGE_NAME) -u $(shell id -u):$(shell id -g)}}*   I do not know if this will still function correctly on other systems. This bug will affect all instances where {{*Docker run*}} is invoked in the makefile.  ></body> </Action>
